                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Montreal</placeName>\n                <date>22 June 5616</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">You will think I have quite forgotten your favor<lb/> of <date>5<hi\n                        rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> inst. which I received the day after\n                    <add>שבועות</add>, but however<lb/> improbable it may appear to you, I have not\n                had a minute<lb/> for letter writing since the holy days. You know I teach<lb/> the\n                children Hebrew, and the number has greatly increased-<lb/>-but you do not wish to\n                know how I have been employed</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">You need not thank me for the almost nothing<lb/> I have done, &amp;\n                would do for any one under the same circumstances.<lb/> The two Daily Prayers sent\n                will I presume soon go, but<lb/> not the Catechisms. If I am to collect the\n                amounts<lb/> due you for Bibles &amp;c you had better enclose me a slip<lb/> which\n                you can send with the next Occidents, something<lb/> in this form. I hereby request\n                &amp; <sic>authorise</sic>\n                <persName>NDS</persName> to<lb/> collect <add>?</add> It is useless to refer in this\n                again to what<lb/> has so long passed, but I am not the only one who<lb/> thinks I\n                had cause to be disappointed in your<lb/> course towards me. You stated in the\n                Occident I had done you<lb/> wrong. I deny this as emphatically now as ever<lb/> My\n                conduct towards you was honest fair and above<lb/> board, although I know you\n                conveyed a different</p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p31g0jf31/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
